<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id749a18d5-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s151102"><num value="151102">§ 151102.</num><heading> Purposes</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The purposes of the corporation are—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id749a18d6-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s151102/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to elevate the character and advance the interests of the profession of teaching; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id749a18d7-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s151102/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to promote the cause of education in the United States.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id749a18d8-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1397">112 Stat. 1397</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
